behind the scenes
=================

* * *

1. background knowledge: python, html, js, css
2. learn [Flask](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/0.12/quickstart/)
3. get an idea of what [jinja](http://jinja.pocoo.org/) is
3. find and download a free [bootstrap](http://getbootstrap.com/) [template](https://www.bootstrapzero.com/bootstrap-template/landing-zero-free-bootstrap-theme)
4. tie the flask python app and bootstrap template
5. follow the instructions on [Heroku](https://devcenter.heroku.com/start)
6. deploy app to the cloud
7. register domain name on [GoDaddy](https://ca.godaddy.com/)
8. set up [custom domain](https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/custom-domains)
on Heroku
9. point custom domain to app with some help from [StackOverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14125175/setup-heroku-and-godaddy
) and this [blogger](http://lifesforlearning.com/heroku-with-godaddy/)
